Requirements:
PHP 5.3 or higher


Documentation:

To use the library you need to add the following code to your application:

// Sets the paths where the autoloader class will look for the classes
set_include_path(implode(PATH_SEPARATOR, array(
    get_include_path(),
    realpath(dirname(__FILE__) . '/SPL'),
)));

// Here we include the autoloader
require 'SPL/Autoload/Autoload.php';

// Namespace alias
use SPL\Autoload\Autoload as Autoload;

// Creating the autoload object
Autoload::registerAutoload();


If you are using CodeIgniter for example and you want the class to not throw an exception when a file for a class is not found you can use the following method:

// Skips the Exception trigger when no file is found for the requested class
Autoload::setSkip(true);


